<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,820,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1873" box="[348,468,820,846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis box="[348,468,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">P. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates “Oritur in Austro-Caledonia, ubi leger. cl. 
<emphasis box="[1061,1156,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Pancher</emphasis>
et 
<emphasis box="[1192,1264,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Sébert</emphasis>
(herb.)”, but the type specimen of this taxon could not be located at 
<collectionCode box="[710,726,857,883]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. There is no reason to believe that it should be located elsewhere since both Pancher and Baillon were affiliated to 
<collectionCode box="[703,719,893,919]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. Type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1873" box="[928,1189,892,918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pancheriana">
<emphasis box="[928,1189,892,918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Polyosma pancheriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described in the same publication, and also a collection of Pancher, is at 
<collectionCode box="[727,743,929,955]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. The specimen may be simply misfiled, particularly after the recent refurbishment of this herbarium, and a 
<typeStatus box="[648,737,965,991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">neotype</typeStatus>
will not be designated at this time. The specimen 
<emphasis box="[1297,1451,964,990]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Balansa 1780</emphasis>
(P-02582518!) bears the handwritten “est? mon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1873" box="[686,806,1000,1026]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis box="[686,806,1000,1026]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">P. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
de herb. Sebert”, which suggests that it has been seen by Baillon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,820,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
In his description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Schlechter (1907)" authorityName=", Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[427,798,1072,1099]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="podophylla">
<emphasis box="[427,582,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">P. podophylla</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlechter, R." box="[597,798,1072,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" pagination="1 - 274" refId="ref4142" refString="Schlechter, R. (1907) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flora von Neu-Kaledonien. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 39: 1 - 274." type="journal article" year="1907">Schlechter (1907)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cited a single collection, 
<collectionCode box="[1092,1114,1072,1098]" country="China" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13092" name="Nanjing University" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">N</collectionCode>
° 15515. There are apparently two sheets at 
<collectionCode box="[298,319,1109,1135]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
, both with “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Pillon, 2018" authorityName="Pillon" authorityYear="2018" box="[467,714,1108,1134]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="podophylla" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[467,714,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Polyosma podophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[724,788,1108,1135]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
” handwritten, but with two different inks. One bears the note “acc. 
<date box="[256,395,1144,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="1903-12-22">22.XII.1903</date>
” (B-100278232) and the other “acc. 
<date box="[812,921,1144,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="1908-01-13">
13. 
<collectionCode box="[844,854,1144,1170]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
.1908
</date>
” (B-100278231). The first one, which is also a better specimen, is chosen as a 
<typeStatus box="[487,593,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<collectionCode box="[604,613,1181,1207]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Guillaumin, A." box="[700,903,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" pagination="174 - 179" refId="ref3576" refString="Guillaumin, A. (1920) Contribution a la flore de la Nouvelle-Caledonie XXX. Plantes recueillies par M. et Mme Le Rat, de 1900 a 1910. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle 26: 174 - 179." type="journal article" year="1920">Guillaumin (1920</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Guillaumin, A." box="[914,971,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" pagination="275 - 278" refId="ref3619" refString="Guillaumin, A. (1939) Materiaux pour la flore de la Nouvelle-Caledonie. LV. - Revision des Saxifragacees. Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 86: 275 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1939.10834175" type="journal article" year="1939">1939</bibRefCitation>
) in treating 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pillon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1108,1261,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="podophylla">
<emphasis box="[1108,1261,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">P. podophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1873" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="discolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">P. discolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
